Cell.Data: The extract data operation is used to extract data out of data sources to populate data marts that can then be queried by researchers. The data sources are typically EMRs. Running this operation will extract data for zero, one or more patients who have consented to make their data available for research. For extracting data a data source may use the FHIR Patient/$everything operation when supported. The operation will be invoked with a POST with the parameters contained within the body of the POST.

The effect of invoking this operation is the creation of a bundle containing the necessary data for zero or more patients. Additionally the Task.status and Task.lastModified times of the instance on which the operation was invoked are updated as part of the execution. Each execution of the Task will create another Task instance (Sub-Task) and when finished will set the Task.parent to be the Task on which the operation was invoked.
This is the reference time based on which the extraction program will retrieve data for only those patients whose records have been created/updated after the referene time.
The reference time will facilitate to get incremental updates performed based on the data that has changed rather than extracting all the data on every extraction run.
When a Patient is specified, the extraction program needs to only extract the data for a specific patient.
If not specified, the extraction program will evaluate all consented patient records based on the reference time to identify the ones that have changed and need to be extracted.

The results of the extraction would provide the data for each patient whose data has been created/updated based on the referenceTime. This data will be in the form of a Bundle which has all the resources that are pertinent for each patient whose data has been extracted.

A list of hints and warnings about problems encountered while extracting the data. These might be show to the user as an advisory note. Note: if the extraction cannot be performed at all, then the operation should fail, and an OperationOutcome is returned directly with the failure, rather than using this parameter.

The load data operation is used to load the data extracted (Bundle) from the extract-data operation into a data mart that can be queried by researchers. The operation will be invoked with a POST with the Bundles as part of the body of the POST.

The effect of invoking this operation is the updation of the patient records within the data mart, along with population of the metadata of the data mart that depends on the extraction process and the creation of provenance records pointing to the resources that are updated as part of the loading process. Additionally the Task.status and Task.lastModified times of the instance on which the operation was invoked are updated as part of the execution. Each execution of the Task will create another Task instance (Sub-Task) and when finished will set the Task.parent to be the Task on which the operation was invoked.
The Bundle resource that contains the extracted data from the extract-data operation is used as input to the load-data operation.

A list of hints and warnings about problems encountered while loading the data. These might be show to the user as an advisory note. Note: if the loading cannot be performed at all, then the operation should fail, and an OperationOutcome is returned directly with the failure, rather than using this parameter.

The execute query operation is used to execute a specific query provided as an input the task. The operation will be invoked with a POST with the information about the OperationDefintion Reference contained within the POST.

The effect of invoking this operation is the creation of a bundle containing the results of the query. Additionally the Task.status and Task.lastModified times of the instance on which the operation was invoked are updated as part of the execution. Each execution of the Task will create another Task instance (Sub-Task) and when finished will set the Task.parent to be the Task on which the operation was invoked.
The Operation Definition will define the type of the query and the parameters that need to be used along with the query.
The Results of the query execution.
